content.p:
"Smart Asset" means a digital representation 
              of rights, obligations, or value that—


(i)
is identified by a cryptographic hash of its genesis document;

(ii)
maintains an append-only receipt chain recording all state transitions;

(iii)
operates according to a deterministic state machine; and

(iv)
conforms to the MASS Protocol specification;

"Settlement Corridor" means a bilateral or 
              multilateral arrangement between Zone participants for the transfer, 
              settlement, or netting of obligations represented as Smart Assets;

"RegPack" means a regulatory compliance package as defined in 
              the MEZ Stack specification, containing sanctions lists, license 
              registries, and compliance calendars;

"LawPack" means a legal text package in Akoma Ntoso format 
              containing the applicable laws, regulations, and model contracts 
              for Zone operations;

The Zone Authority shall have power to—


(a)
register entities to operate within the Zone;

(b)
issue, suspend, and revoke licenses;

(c)
approve Settlement Corridors;

(d)
maintain the Zone's RegPack and LawPack;

(e)
enforce compliance with this Act and regulations; and

(f)
do all things necessary for the proper administration of the Zone.
